        <abstract>
            <para>The Marie-Victorin Herbarium (MT) is the second largest university herbarium in Quebec and ranks fourth among all Canadian herbaria. It includes about 50,000&amp;#43; bryophytes. About half of the material is Canadian, but representation is global. The current dataset includes the ca. 28,700 digitized specimens from the collection.</para>
        </abstract>
